# weave.word — what a weave IS: the chains a being reads in a moment, folded into its view.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the host (the reels one fold read, sealed on Act.innerFace.weave). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, history.word, fold.word. Every word grounded (weave, fold,
# chain, history, world). `moment` is the floor (time). The deeper world, the one beings' folds
# AGREE on, waits for `being`, the perspective that makes agreement mean anything.

A weave is the chains a being reads in one moment, those it can see and those where it stands.
A weave is that being's view of the moment, folded from the chains it read, and kept.
